Part1:
Create an Azure Databricks workspace from Azure Portal
Launch Databricks workspace
Create a Single Node Cluster
Attach cluster to a notebook
Run a basic Spark command - spark.range(1, 50).count() 
Show its output
 
Part 2:
Create a Storage Account (ADLS Gen2)
Upload a CSV file: Employees.csv
Configure access using SAS Token
Read data using Spark
Part3:
Select specific columns
Filter employees with salary > 50,000
Add a derived column (New Column) Tax
Save transformed data as Delta Table
Part4:
Update records in Delta table
View Delta table history
Check the updated data with Change Data Feed

Part5: 
Show a dashboard with Department wise - Average Salary
